reviewText:
CONS
- graphics feels like $2 game;
- sound feels like $2 game;
- slightly annoying degrading skills, needs regular repetitive top up (but game might be too easy otherwise);
- consequences of being caught not harsh enough, they just take away yr contraband;
- not random gen only 9 fixed prison layouts so far, once u've worked out a prison it's quite easy but a prison editor is in the works;
- leaderboard has ppl breaking out in 1 day on the easier lvls;

PROS
+ wickedly fun gameplay;
+ great escape from prison atmos;
+ good chilling music, i rarely leave game music on;
+ numerous ways to escape not just one route;

Don't be fooled by graphics, the devs done a great job on the gameplay. I'm totally immersed in the prison break atmos. Started digging a tunnel to freedom while everyone's working mwahahaha...balls! Guards are coming to check my room! Everything in my room is contraband!?!?!? It wasn't me!! Noooo don't put me in solitaryyyyy. If only triple AAA games put some of this effort into games.

Some of the leveling up minigames are a little repetitive as they degrade over time, but the game would probably be too easy otherwise. It is an indie game so it does feel a little light in some areas, there's not a great deal of items but they are rare to come around, some of the logic is very dodgy eg, u can beat up a guard and take his gear but there isn't any harsh consequences. But it's great fun to hatch out an escape plan and literally chipping away, making sure yr timing is executed perfectly.

At current price I'd probably won't recommend if not for the devs adding a prison editor (not sure if free update or dlc). The prisons feel varied enough but once u've worked one out, replayability is left upto u to escape differently.
